## Artifact Readiness Gate

Use this gate before treating the NFR artifact as review-ready, delivery-ready, production-ready, or approved. Link the target when it exists. If a target does not exist yet, list the missing target in Evidence or Assumptions, Risks, And Open Questions.

| Gate Item | Required Evidence / Link | Status | Owner | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Source request / ticket linked | Markdown link to source request, ticket, review finding, or change driver. | Missing / Linked | Artifact owner | Required before Review-ready. |
| Upstream BRD/PRD/FR artifacts linked | Markdown links to upstream BRD, PRD, FRD, or product-scope artifacts. | Missing / Partial / Linked | `ai-product-manager` / `ai-business-analyst` | Required before Delivery-ready. |
| Backlog/story linked | Markdown link to backlog item, story, or delivery scope record. | Missing / Linked | Product / delivery owner | Required before Delivery-ready. |
| All referenced FR IDs verified | Every referenced FR ID exists in the linked source artifact. | Unverified / Verified | Artifact owner | Delivery-ready is forbidden while unresolved. |
| Security/legal blockers resolved or marked production-blocking | Security, privacy, legal, regulatory, and data-residency blockers are closed, excepted, or marked `Production blocker`. | Open / Production blocker / Resolved | `ai-security-engineer` / legal owner | Production-ready is forbidden while open. |
| Workload baselines available or draft-only | Workload baseline evidence exists, or all affected targets are marked `Draft target`. | Missing / Draft-only / Available | `ai-platform-engineer` / data owner | Required for final numeric targets. |
| Validation/test evidence targets linked | Validation plan links expected test, dashboard, audit, security, or release evidence targets. | Missing / Partial / Linked | `ai-quality-engineer` / evidence owner | Required before Delivery-ready. |
| Approval status | One of: Draft / Review-ready / Delivery-ready / Production-ready / Approved. | Draft | Artifact owner / approver | Status may advance only when preceding gate criteria are satisfied. |

## Reference Integrity Check

- Every BRD, PRD, FR, NFR, story, test, and evidence ID must be a Markdown link when the target exists.
- No phantom IDs are allowed. For example, do not reference `FR-009` unless `FR-009` exists in a linked source artifact.
- Missing links, missing source artifacts, unresolved IDs, and unverified references must be listed as evidence gaps.
- Delivery-ready status is forbidden while source IDs are unresolved, unlinked, or unverified.

