## Security And Privacy Approval Gate

Complete this gate for systems with personal, sensitive, regulated, operationally critical, evidence, export, integration, or security-relevant data. If not applicable, record `Not applicable` with rationale and approval owner.

| Control Area | Required Decision / Evidence | Status | Approval Owner | Evidence Link |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Data classification | Classification for personal, sensitive, regulated, operational, evidence, audit, export, and integration data. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | `ai-security-engineer` / data owner | Link or gap |
| Lawful basis | Lawful basis for processing personal or regulated data. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | Legal / privacy owner | Link or gap |
| Consent / notice | User, employee, customer, vendor, or stakeholder notice and consent approach where applicable. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | Legal / product owner | Link or gap |
| UAE data residency | Residency requirement, hosting region, transfer restriction, and exception decision. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | `ai-security-engineer` / platform owner | Link or gap |
| Retention / deletion / archive rule | Retention period, deletion trigger, archive policy, and evidence handling. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | Data owner / records owner | Link or gap |
| Encryption | Encryption in transit, at rest, backup, evidence storage, and key ownership. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | `ai-security-engineer` / platform owner | Link or gap |
| Masking / redaction | UI, API, report, notification, integration, and support-view masking rules. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | `ai-security-engineer` / product owner | Link or gap |
| Export / log redaction | Export, report, telemetry, trace, audit, and application-log redaction rules. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | `ai-security-engineer` / implementation owner | Link or gap |
| Access roles | Role model, privileged access, segregation of duties, and exception handling. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | `ai-security-engineer` / product owner | Link or gap |
| Audit | Audit events, retention, access, review owner, and investigation evidence. | Unknown / Draft / Approved / Not applicable | `ai-security-engineer` / operations owner | Link or gap |

## Template Use Notes

- Ask the requester for missing values before generation when a `TBD` would affect a quality target, threshold, workload, data classification, availability target, evidence owner, or production gate.
- No `TBD` may remain when status is `Approved` or `Ready for delivery` unless it is listed in Assumptions, Risks, And Open Questions with an owner, needed-by date, and blocker/exception status.
- Classify data before applying privacy/security blockers. If the product has no personal, sensitive, regulated, operationally critical, or security-relevant data, record privacy controls as `Not applicable` with rationale instead of leaving a blocker.
- Keep authoring instructions out of generated artifact rows. Replace example workflow names and placeholder thresholds with source-derived FR IDs, workload assumptions, and measurable targets.
- Every draft numeric target must explicitly say `Draft target`.
- Every final numeric target must have linked baseline evidence and named owner approval.
- If baseline evidence is missing, the requirement readiness status must be `Draft` or `Conditional`, not `Ready`, `Production-ready`, or `Approved`.

