## Validation Plan

| Validation Area | Evidence Required | Exit Criteria |
|---|---|---|
| Performance and workload | Load/API/browser/batch timing report covering core workflows, reports, imports/exports, and integrations where applicable. | Performance NFRs meet p95/p90 targets or exceptions are approved. |
| Availability and recovery | Health checks, uptime dashboard, backup/restore, planned-maintenance record, fallback/failover drill when applicable, import/reconciliation after fallback when applicable. | Availability/recovery NFRs met; fallback is approved, staffed, drilled, and evidenced before go-live where required. |
| Security and privacy | Security review, authorization matrix tests, masking/encryption evidence, retention/deletion evidence, export/log redaction evidence, upload-control evidence when applicable, local/non-federated account policy approval when applicable. | Security/privacy NFRs accepted by `ai-security-engineer`; production blockers closed or formally excepted before production. |
| Capacity and scalability | Capacity model, data growth forecast, storage estimate, load/throughput test when applicable. | Capacity/scalability NFRs met or marked not applicable with rationale. |
| Audit and data integrity | Audit event samples, database/storage constraint review, import/export validation report, reconciliation evidence. | Audit and data integrity NFRs met with no critical gaps. |
| Usability/accessibility/compatibility | Timed UAT notes, critical task failure log, accessibility scan, keyboard/focus review, viewport/browser/channel matrix. | Usability p90 thresholds met; 0 critical task failures; no critical accessibility/compatibility defects. |
| Observability and readiness | Dashboard/log evidence, alert dry run, trace sample, release evidence pack, exception register. | Operational readiness evidence complete and owned. |

